27 (3) Subject to appropriation by the Legislature, the
28 program shall provide assistance in the form of grants to
29 residents experiencing economic hardship. Such grants must be
30 available to residents if any of the following occurs:
31 (a) Utility costs rise above a specified percentage of
32 average household income.
33 (b) Property insurance premiums rise above a specified
34 threshold.
35 (c) Statewide unemployment rises above a specified
36 percentage.
37 (d) An economic decline causes widespread hardship.
38 (e) A natural disaster leads to the declaration of a state
39 of emergency.
40 (4) To be eligible for assistance under the program, an
41 individual must:
42 (a) Have been a resident of this state for at least 1 year
43 before applying;
44 (b) Provide evidence of a change in circumstances which
45 hinders or prohibits the individual from being able to fulfill
46 pending financial obligations related to utility, property
47 insurance, childcare, or health care expenses; and
48 (c) Provide documentation of utility costs, property
49 insurance premiums, childcare expenses, or health care expenses.
